Constructs a new, empty `Vec<T, A>`.

The vector will not allocate until elements are pushed onto it.

# Examples

```
#![feature(allocator_api)]

use std::alloc::System;

# #[allow(unused_mut)]
let mut vec: Vec<i32, _> = Vec::new_in(System);
```
